embedded.html#ImageElement.summary: The <image> SVG element includes images inside SVG documents. It can display raster image files or other SVG files.
embedded.html#ImageElement.title: <image>

shapes.html#LineElement.name: line
shapes.html#LineElement.summary: The <line> element is an SVG basic shape used to create a line connecting two points.
shapes.html#LineElement.title: <line>

pservers.html#LinearGradientElementGradi.name: gradientTransform
pservers.html#LinearGradientElementGradi.summary: The gradientTransform attribute contains the definition of an optional additional transformation from the gradient coordinate system onto the target coordinate system (i.e., userSpaceOnUse or objectBoundingBox). This allows for things such as skewing the gradient. This additional transformation matrix is post-multiplied to (i.e., inserted to the right of) any previously defined transformations, including the implicit transformation necessary to convert from object bounding box units to user space.
pservers.html#LinearGradientElementGradi.title: gradientTransform

pservers.html#RadialGradientElementGradi.name: gradientTransform
pservers.html#RadialGradientElementGradi.summary: The gradientTransform attribute contains the definition of an optional additional transformation from the gradient coordinate system onto the target coordinate system (i.e., userSpaceOnUse or objectBoundingBox). This allows for things such as skewing the gradient. This additional transformation matrix is post-multiplied to (i.e., inserted to the right of) any previously defined transformations, including the implicit transformation necessary to convert from object bounding box units to user space.
pservers.html#RadialGradientElementGradi.title: gradientTransform

pservers.html#LinearGradientElementSprea.name: spreadMethod

pservers.html#LinearGradients.name: linearGradient
pservers.html#LinearGradients.summary: The <linearGradient> element lets authors define linear gradients to apply to other SVG elements.
pservers.html#LinearGradients.title: <linearGradient>

painting.html#MarkerHeightAttribute.name: markerHeight
painting.html#MarkerHeightAttribute.summary: The markerHeight attribute represents the height of the viewport into which the <marker> is to be fitted when it is rendered according to the viewBox and preserveAspectRatio attributes.
painting.html#MarkerHeightAttribute.title: markerHeight

painting.html#MarkerUnitsAttribute.name: markerUnits
painting.html#MarkerUnitsAttribute.summary: The markerUnits attribute defines the coordinate system for the markerWidth and markerHeight attributes and the contents of the <marker>.
painting.html#MarkerUnitsAttribute.title: markerUnits

painting.html#MarkerWidthAttribute.name: markerWidth
painting.html#MarkerWidthAttribute.summary: The markerWidth attribute represents the width of the viewport into which the <marker> is to be fitted when it is rendered according to the viewBox and preserveAspectRatio attributes.
painting.html#MarkerWidthAttribute.title: markerWidth

painting.html#OrientAttribute.name: orient
painting.html#OrientAttribute.summary: The orient attribute indicates how a marker is rotated when it is placed at its position on the shape.
painting.html#OrientAttribute.title: orient

painting.html#MarkerElement.name: marker
painting.html#MarkerElement.summary: The <marker> element defines a graphic used for drawing arrowheads or polymarkers on a given <path>, <line>, <polyline> or <polygon> element.
painting.html#MarkerElement.title: <marker>

struct.html#MetadataElement.name: metadata
struct.html#MetadataElement.summary: The <metadata> SVG element adds metadata to SVG content. Metadata is structured information about data. The contents of <metadata> should be elements from other XML namespaces such as RDF, FOAF, etc.
struct.html#MetadataElement.title: <metadata>

paths.html#DProperty.name: d
paths.html#DProperty.summary: The d attribute defines a path to be drawn.
paths.html#DProperty.title: d

paths.html#PathElement.name: path
paths.html#PathElement.summary: The <path> SVG element is the generic element to define a shape. All the basic shapes can be created with a path element.
paths.html#PathElement.title: <path>

pservers.html#PatternElementPatternConte.name: patternContentUnits
pservers.html#PatternElementPatternConte.summary: The patternContentUnits attribute indicates which coordinate system to use for the contents of the <pattern> element.
pservers.html#PatternElementPatternConte.title: patternContentUnits

pservers.html#PatternElementPatternTrans.name: patternTransform
pservers.html#PatternElementPatternTrans.summary: The patternTransform attribute defines a list of transform definitions that are applied to a pattern tile.
pservers.html#PatternElementPatternTrans.title: patternTransform

pservers.html#PatternElementPatternUnits.name: patternUnits
pservers.html#PatternElementPatternUnits.summary: The patternUnits attribute indicates which coordinate system to use for the geometry properties of the <pattern> element.
pservers.html#PatternElementPatternUnits.title: patternUnits

pservers.html#Patterns.name: pattern
pservers.html#Patterns.summary: The <pattern> element defines a graphics object which can be redrawn at repeated x- and y-coordinate intervals ("tiled") to cover an area.
pservers.html#Patterns.title: <pattern>

shapes.html#PolygonElement.name: polygon
shapes.html#PolygonElement.summary: The <polygon> element defines a closed shape consisting of a set of connected straight line segments. The last point is connected to the first point.
shapes.html#PolygonElement.title: <polygon>

shapes.html#PolylineElement.name: polyline
shapes.html#PolylineElement.summary: The <polyline> SVG element is an SVG basic shape that creates straight lines connecting several points. Typically a polyline is used to create open shapes as the last point doesn't have to be connected to the first point. For closed shapes see the <polygon> element.
shapes.html#PolylineElement.title: <polyline>

pservers.html#RadialGradientElementFRAtt.name: fr
pservers.html#RadialGradientElementFRAtt.summary: The fr attribute defines the radius of the focal point for the radial gradient.
pservers.html#RadialGradientElementFRAtt.title: fr

pservers.html#RadialGradientElementFXAtt.name: fx
pservers.html#RadialGradientElementFXAtt.summary: The fx attribute defines the x-axis coordinate of the focal point for a radial gradient.
pservers.html#RadialGradientElementFXAtt.title: fx

pservers.html#RadialGradientElementFYAtt.name: fy
pservers.html#RadialGradientElementFYAtt.summary: The fy attribute defines the y-axis coordinate of the focal point for a radial gradient.
pservers.html#RadialGradientElementFYAtt.title: fy

pservers.html#RadialGradients.name: radialGradient
pservers.html#RadialGradients.summary: The <radialGradient> element lets authors define radial gradients that can be applied to fill or stroke of graphical elements.
pservers.html#RadialGradients.title: <radialGradient>

shapes.html#RectElement.name: rect
shapes.html#RectElement.summary: The <rect> element is a basic SVG shape that draws rectangles, defined by their position, width, and height. The rectangles may have their corners rounded.
shapes.html#RectElement.title: <rect>

interact.html#ScriptElement.name: script
interact.html#ScriptElement.summary: The SVG script element allows to add scripts to an SVG document.
interact.html#ScriptElement.title: <script>

pservers.html#StopOpacityProperty.name: stop-opacity
pservers.html#StopOpacityProperty.summary: The stop-opacity attribute defines the opacity of a given color gradient stop.
pservers.html#StopOpacityProperty.title: stop-opacity

pservers.html#GradientStops.name: stop
pservers.html#GradientStops.summary: The SVG <stop> element defines a color and its position to use on a gradient. This element is always a child of a <linearGradient> or <radialGradient> element.
pservers.html#GradientStops.title: <stop>

styling.html#StyleElementMediaAttribute.name: media
styling.html#StyleElementMediaAttribute.summary: The media attribute specifies a media query that must be matched for a style sheet to apply.
styling.html#StyleElementMediaAttribute.title: media

styling.html#StyleElement.name: style
styling.html#StyleElement.summary: The SVG <style> element allows style sheets to be embedded directly within SVG content.
styling.html#StyleElement.title: <style>

struct.html#NewDocument.name: svg
struct.html#NewDocument.summary: The svg element is a container that defines a new coordinate system and viewport. It is used as the outermost element of SVG documents, but it can also be used to embed an SVG fragment inside an SVG or HTML document.
struct.html#NewDocument.title: <svg>

struct.html#SwitchElement.name: switch
struct.html#SwitchElement.summary: The <switch> SVG element evaluates any requiredFeatures, requiredExtensions and systemLanguage attributes on its direct child elements in order, and then renders the first child where these attributes evaluate to true.
struct.html#SwitchElement.title: <switch>

struct.html#SymbolElement.name: symbol
struct.html#SymbolElement.summary: The <symbol> element is used to define graphical template objects which can be instantiated by a <use> element.
struct.html#SymbolElement.title: <symbol>

text.html#TextElementDXAttribute.name: dx
text.html#TextElementDXAttribute.summary: The dx attribute indicates a shift along the x-axis on the position of an element or its content.
text.html#TextElementDXAttribute.title: dx

text.html#TextElementDYAttribute.name: dy
text.html#TextElementDYAttribute.summary: The dy attribute indicates a shift along the y-axis on the position of an element or its content.
text.html#TextElementDYAttribute.title: dy

text.html#TextElementLengthAdjustAttribu.name: lengthAdjust
text.html#TextElementLengthAdjustAttribu.summary: The lengthAdjust attribute controls how the text is stretched into the length defined by the textLength attribute.
text.html#TextElementLengthAdjustAttribu.title: lengthAdjust

text.html#TextElementXAttribute.name: x
text.html#TextElementXAttribute.summary: The x attribute defines an x-axis coordinate in the user coordinate system.
text.html#TextElementXAttribute.title: x

text.html#TextElementYAttribute.name: y
text.html#TextElementYAttribute.summary: The y attribute defines a y-axis coordinate in the user coordinate system.
text.html#TextElementYAttribute.title: y

text.html#TextElement.name: text
text.html#TextElement.summary: The SVG <text> element draws a graphics element consisting of text. It's possible to apply a gradient, pattern, clipping path, mask, or filter to <text>, like any other SVG graphics element.
text.html#TextElement.title: <text>

text.html#TextElement.name: tspan
text.html#TextElement.summary: The SVG <tspan> element defines a subtext within a <text> element or another <tspan> element. It allows for adjustment of the style and/or position of that subtext as needed.
text.html#TextElement.title: <tspan>

text.html#TextPathElementSideAttribute.name: side
text.html#TextPathElementSideAttribute.summary: The side attribute determines the side of a path the text is placed on (relative to the path direction).
text.html#TextPathElementSideAttribute.title: side

text.html#TextPathElementSpacingAttribut.name: spacing
text.html#TextPathElementSpacingAttribut.summary: The spacing attribute indicates how the user agent should determine the spacing between typographic characters that are to be rendered along a path.
text.html#TextPathElementSpacingAttribut.title: spacing

text.html#TextPathElementStartOffsetAttr.name: startOffset
text.html#TextPathElementStartOffsetAttr.summary: The startOffset attribute defines an offset from the start of the path for the initial current text position along the path after converting the path to the <textPath> element's coordinate system.
text.html#TextPathElementStartOffsetAttr.title: startOffset

text.html#TextPathElement.name: textPath
text.html#TextPathElement.summary: To render text along the shape of a <path>, enclose the text in a <textPath> element that has an href attribute with a reference to the <path> element.

safari.notes: Until Safari 6, textPath was not re-rendered when the referenced path was changed dynamically (see bug 15799)

text.html#TextPathElement.title: <textPath>

struct.html#TitleElement.name: title
struct.html#TitleElement.summary: The <title> element provides an accessible, short-text description of any SVG container element or graphics element.
struct.html#TitleElement.title: <title>  the SVG accessible name element

struct.html#UseElement.name: use
struct.html#UseElement.summary: The <use> element takes nodes from within the SVG document, and duplicates them somewhere else. The effect is the same as if the nodes were deeply cloned into a non-exposed DOM, then pasted where the use element is, much like cloned template elements.

firefox.notes: Before version 56, Firefox does not completely follow the use cascading rules (see bug 265894). A fix is documented by Amelia Bellamy-Royds on StackOverflow.

struct.html#UseElement.title: <use>

linking.html#ViewElement.name: view
linking.html#ViewElement.summary: A view is a defined way to view the image, like a zoom level or a detail view.
linking.html#ViewElement.title: <view>
